ProMED-mail promed@promedmail.org







[While these reports represent 2 new areas of finding the disease, it does not sound like it was unexpected. After all, the hunt areas overlap or border areas where the disease has been previously identified.

It would be nice if there were a vaccine for this disease. Perhaps an oral vaccine similar to the oral rabies vaccines for some wildlife can be devised. One has to wonder for how long they have been trying to find a cure or a vaccine and how many research dollars have been used on this type of endeavor? - Mod.TG

Wyoming may be found at: http://healthmap.org/r/awGp - Mod.TG]
